title: Czech Republic Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Czech Republic Three Month Interbank Rate was at 0.17 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in Czech Republic averaged 4.07 percent from 1992 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 27.63 percent in June of 1997 and a record low of 0.15 percent in January of 2016. In Czech Republic, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Czech Republic Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Czech Financial Benchmark Facility
